"navVariant":"base","head":{"title":"Debt recovery | MOONSTONE ADVOCATES","description":"Recover unpaid invoices quickly and effectively with our debt recovery solicitors. We help businesses protect cash flow and secure payment. Contact us today.","ogTitle":"Debt recovery | MOONSTONE ADVOCATES","ogDescription":"Recover unpaid invoices quickly and effectively with our debt recovery solicitors. We help businesses protect cash flow and secure payment. Contact us today.","ogType":"website","twitterCard":"summary_large_image","canonical":"debt-recovery.html","jsonLd":["{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"WebPage\",\n  \"name\": \"Debt recovery\",\n  \"description\": \"Recover unpaid invoices quickly and effectively with our debt recovery solicitors. We help businesses protect cash flow and secure payment.\",\n  \"url\": \"/debt-recovery\",\n  \"inLanguage\": \"en\",\n  \"about\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Service\",\n    \"name\": \"Debt Recovery Services\",\n    \"description\": \"Professional debt recovery services for businesses recovering unpaid invoices up to £100,000 in England and Wales, including pre-issue letters, court proceedings, enforcement, and insolvency proceedings.\",\n    \"provider\": {\n      \"@type\": \"LegalService\",\n      \"name\": \"MOONSTONE ADVOCATES\",\n      \"address\": {\n        \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n        \"streetAddress\": \"City Point, 29 King Street\",\n        \"addressLocality\": \"Kampala\",\n        \"postalCode\": \"LS1 2HL\",\n        \"addressCountry\": \"GB\"\n      },\n      \"telephone\": \"0113 207 0000\",\n      \"areaServed\": [\n        \"England\",\n        \"Wales\"\n      ]\n    },\n    \"serviceType\": \"Debt Recovery\",\n    \"offers\": [\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Letter Before Action\",\n        \"description\": \"Pre-issue stage including reviewing documents, drafting and sending Letter Before Action, considering debtor's response, and advising on next steps\",\n        \"price\": \"220\",\n        \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\",\n        \"priceSpecification\": {\n          \"@type\": \"PriceSpecification\",\n          \"minPrice\": \"220\",\n          \"maxPrice\": \"660\",\n          \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Issuing a Claim Form (Money Claim Online)\",\n        \"description\": \"Fixed fee for issuing straightforward claims online via Money Claim Online\",\n        \"price\": \"220\",\n        \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Judgment Request\",\n        \"description\": \"Requesting judgment when debtor does not respond or admits claim in full\",\n        \"price\": \"110\",\n        \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Statutory Demand\",\n        \"description\": \"Drafting and serving statutory demand including process server fee\",\n        \"priceSpecification\": {\n          \"@type\": \"PriceSpecification\",\n          \"minPrice\": \"745\",\n          \"maxPrice\": \"1030\",\n          \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Bankruptcy Proceedings\",\n        \"description\": \"Individual debt bankruptcy proceedings including statutory demand service, court fees, and advocate representation\",\n        \"priceSpecification\": {\n          \"@type\": \"PriceSpecification\",\n          \"minPrice\": \"4000\",\n          \"maxPrice\": \"4700\",\n          \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"name\": \"Winding-up Proceedings\",\n        \"description\": \"Company debt winding-up proceedings including court fees, advertising, and advocate representation\",\n        \"priceSpecification\": {\n          \"@type\": \"PriceSpecification\",\n          \"minPrice\": \"5250\",\n          \"maxPrice\": \"6500\",\n          \"priceCurrency\": \"GBP\"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"]},"blocks":[{"tag":"main","attrs":{"fade":"target","className":"main-wrapper"},"html":"<div><header class=\"section_header62\"><div class=\"padding-global\"><div class=\"container-large\"><div class=\"padding-section-large is-page-top\"><div class=\"header62_component\"><div class=\"text-align-center\"><div class=\"max-width-large\"><div class=\"margin-bottom margin-small\"><h1 class=\"heading-style-h1\">Debt recovery  </h1></div><p class=\"text-size-medium\">This guidance explains the basis of our charges for debt recovery work where the debt value is <strong>up to £100,000</strong> and the debtor is based in <strong>England and Wales</strong>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></header><section class=\"section_text\"><div class=\"padding-global\"><div class=\"container-small\"><div class=\"padding-section-large\"><div class=\"text_component\"><div><header class=\"section_team-profile-large_header-1\"><div class=\"w-richtext\"><p>This guidance sets out:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Our total costs (or average or range where a total cannot be given)</li><li>Likely disbursements</li><li>What services are included at each key stage</li><li>The key stages of the debt recovery process and likely timescales</li></ul><p>Every case is unique and cost or timescale may vary depending on complexity or how long the matter progresses.</p><p>‍</p><h4>The team</h4><p>The Debt Recovery team has extensive experience in debt recovery and court procedure. The team is supervised by a Partner.</p><p>‍</p><p>The Insolvency team works alongside the Debt Recovery team and includes a Senior Associate Solicitor and a Solicitor.</p><p>‍</p><h4>Debt Recovery ream members and rates (exclusive of VAT)</h4><ul role=\"list\"><li><strong>Tina Eyles – Paralegal</strong><br>Hourly rate: £220<br>Experience: 18 years as a Paralegal, including 5 years in debt recovery</li><li><strong>Andrew Morgan – Senior Associate Solicitor</strong><br>Hourly rate: £320<br>Experience: 9 years</li><li><strong>Yat Wong – Senior Associate Solicitor</strong><br>Hourly rate: £330<br>Experience: 30 years</li><li><strong>James Martin – Legal Director</strong><br>Hourly rate: £330<br>Experience: 15 years</li><li><strong>LUgandae Patel – Partner</strong><br>Hourly rate: £370<br>Experience: 29 years</li></ul><h4>Insolvency team members and rates (exclusive of VAT)</h4><ul role=\"list\"><li><strong>Victoria Tynan – Solicitor</strong><br>Hourly rate: £270<br>Experience: 5 years</li><li><strong>Ian Scobbie – Senior Associate Solicitor</strong><br>Hourly rate: £360<br>Experience: over 30 years</li></ul><p>VAT is charged at the prevailing rate, currently <strong>20%</strong>.</p><p>‍</p><h4>Costs overview</h4><p>Debt recovery work is generally charged on an <strong>hourly rate basis</strong>. The figures below are estimates. Costs may increase if a matter becomes protracted or more complex.</p><p>‍</p><p>Some fees may be recoverable from the debtor if your claim is successful.</p><p>‍</p><h4>1. Pre-issue stage</h4><h5>1a. Letter Before Action</h5><p>This stage includes:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Reviewing documents</li><li>Drafting and sending a Letter Before Action</li><li>Considering the debtor’s response</li><li>Advising on next steps</li></ul><p>We aim to send the Letter Before Action within <strong>5 working days</strong> of receiving all required information.<br>The debtor has <strong>14 days</strong> to respond if they are an individual, or <strong>30 days</strong> if they are a company.<br>Advice is provided within <strong>5 working days</strong> of receiving any response.</p><p>‍</p><p><strong>Estimated fees (exclusive of VAT):</strong></p><ul role=\"list\"><li>For debts up to £25,000: between <strong>£220 and £440</strong></li><li>For debts between £25,000 and £100,000: between <strong>£220 and £660</strong></li></ul><p>There are no disbursements at this stage.</p><p>‍</p><p>The typical timescale is <strong>4 to 12 weeks</strong> from the date of instruction.</p><p>‍</p><p>These costs do <strong>not</strong> include negotiating settlement with the debtor.</p><p>‍</p><h5>1b. Pre-issue discussions/negotiations</h5><p>This covers negotiations with the debtor after the Letter Before Action and before issuing court proceedings. This may include telephone calls, letters, or emails.</p><p>‍</p><p>Work is charged at the applicable hourly rate.</p><p>‍<br>We would not normally expect these discussions to exceed <strong>2 to 3 hours over approximately 4 weeks</strong>.</p><p><strong>Estimated fees (exclusive of VAT):</strong></p><ul role=\"list\"><li>For debts up to £100,000: between <strong>£440 and £660</strong></li></ul><p>There are no disbursements at this stage.</p><p>‍</p><h4>2. Post-Issue Stage</h4><p>If the debtor does not respond to the Letter Before Action, or disputes the debt and negotiations break down, County Court proceedings can be issued.</p><p>‍</p><p>Please note that after proceedings are issued, it can take <strong>12 to 18 months</strong> for a final hearing to be listed.</p><p>‍</p><h5>2a. Issuing a Claim Form (Money Claim Online)</h5><p>‍</p><p>This assumes the claim is straightforward and issued online via Money Claim Online, without the need for separate Particulars of Claim.</p><p>‍</p><p><strong>Our fixed fee for issuing the claim</strong> is <strong>£220 plus VAT</strong>.</p><p>‍</p><p><strong>Court fees depend on the debt value</strong>, for example:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Up to £300: court fee £35</li><li>£300 to £500: court fee £50</li><li>£500 to £1,000: court fee £70</li><li>£1,000 to £1,500: court fee £80</li><li>£1,500 to £3,000: court fee £115</li><li>£3,000 to £5,000: court fee £205</li><li>£5,000 to £10,000: court fee £455</li><li>£10,000 to £100,000: court fee is <strong>5% of the claim value</strong></li></ul><p>The claim is usually submitted for issued within <strong>5 working days</strong> once all information is received.</p><p>‍</p><h5>2b. Defence</h5><p>If the debtor files a Defence, the matter may be transferred to a Solicitor in the Dispute Resolution team. At that stage:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>You will receive a tailored cost estimate</li><li>You will be advised whether it is economical to pursue the claim</li><li>Prospects of success will be assessed</li></ul><p>If the case proceeds to a final hearing, a court hearing fee will apply depending on the claim value:</p><p>‍</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Small claims up to £300: court fee £27</li><li>Small claims between £300 to £500: court fee £59</li><li>Small claims between £500 to £1,000: court fee £85</li><li>Small claims between £1,000 to £1,500: court fee £123</li><li>Small claims between £1,500 to £3,000: court fee £181.00</li><li>Small claims over £3,000: court fee £346</li><li>Fast track claims: court fee £455</li><li>Intermediate or multi track claims: £1,334</li></ul><ul role=\"list\">‍</ul><ul role=\"list\"></ul><ul role=\"list\"></ul><p>A defended matter typically takes <strong>12 to 18 months</strong> to reach a final hearing.</p><p>‍</p><h5>2c. Judgment</h5><p>If the debtor does not respond to the claim or admits it in full, you can request judgment.</p><p><strong>Our fee</strong> for requesting judgment is <strong>£110 plus VAT</strong>, regardless of the debt value (up to £100,000).</p><p>‍</p><p>There are no disbursements at this stage.</p><p>‍</p><p>Judgment is usually entered within <strong>12 weeks</strong>, and often sooner.</p><p>‍<br>The process of requesting judgment itself takes <strong>1 to 2 weeks</strong>.</p><p>‍</p><p>This does not include dealing with any application by the debtor to set aside judgment.</p><p>‍</p><h4>3. Enforcement</h4><p>If the judgment is not paid, enforcement options are available. Fees below assume the debtor does <strong>not</strong> contest enforcement.</p><p>‍</p><h5>Available enforcement options include:</h5><ul role=\"list\"><li><strong>Charging Order</strong><br>Disbursements include Land Registry search fees and court fees.<br>Total estimated cost: between £583 and £803 <strong>plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>12 weeks</strong></li><li><strong>County Court Bailiffs</strong><br>Disbursments include: court fee<br>Total estimated cost: approximately <strong>£274 plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>3 to 12 months</strong></li><li><strong>High Court Enforcement</strong><br>Disbursements include: court fee and abortive fee if enforcement unsuccessful.<br>Estimated total cost: between <strong>£520 and £815 plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>3 to 12 months</strong></li><li><strong>Third Party Debt Order</strong><br>Includes court fees and advocate attendance.<br>Estimated total cost: approximately <strong>£945 plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>12 weeks</strong></li><li><strong>Attachment of Earnings Order</strong><br>Estimated total cost: between <strong>£355 and £555 plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>12 weeks</strong></li><li><strong>Order to Obtain Information from a Debtor</strong><br>Includes court issue fee and bailiff service.<br>Estimated total cost: between <strong>£642 and £862 plus VAT</strong><br>Timescale: approximately <strong>12 weeks</strong></li></ul><p>Enforcement usually takes <strong>3 to 12 months</strong>, but payment is not guaranteed and depends on the debtor’s assets or ability to pay.</p><p>‍</p><p>Negotiations after enforcement has commenced are charged separately on an hourly rate basis.</p><p>‍</p><h4>4. Insolvency proceedings</h4><p>Insolvency proceedings may be used instead of County Court proceedings or as an alternative enforcement method, but only where the debt is <strong>not disputed</strong>.</p><p>‍</p><h5>Statutory demand</h5><p>Includes:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Drafting</li><li>Process server fee</li><li>Total estimated cost: between <strong>£745 and £1,030 plus VAT</strong></li></ul><p>We aim to arrange service within <strong>5 working days</strong> of receiving information.</p><h5>‍</h5><h5>Bankruptcy proceedings (individual debt)</h5><p>Includes:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Service of Statutory Demand</li><li>Bankruptcy search</li><li>Court issue fee</li><li>Official Receiver deposit (refundable if dismissed)</li><li>Service of Bankruptcy Petition</li><li>Advocate fee at hearing</li></ul><p><strong>Total estimated cost:</strong> between <strong>£4,000 and £4,700 plus VAT.</strong></p><p>‍</p><p>The timescale is typically <strong>2 to 3 months</strong> from service of the Statutory Demand to hearing.</p><p>‍</p><h5>Winding-up proceedings (company debt)</h5><p>Includes:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Company search</li><li>Court issue fee</li><li>Official Receiver deposit (refundable if dismissed)</li><li>Advertising in the London Gazette</li><li>Service of the petition</li><li>Advocate representation at hearing</li></ul><p><strong>Total estimated cost:</strong> between <strong>£5,250 and £6,500 plus VAT.</strong></p><p>‍</p><p>A winding-up hearing usually takes place <strong>6 to 8 weeks</strong> after the petition is issued.</p><p>‍</p><p>Costs do not include dealing with:</p><ul role=\"list\"><li>Applications to set aside a Statutory Demand</li><li>Injunctions to restrain presentation or advertisement of a winding-up petition</li></ul><p>Any such work is charged at hourly rates and an estimate will be provided.</p><p>‍</p><p><strong>MOONSTONE ADVOCATES</strong><br><strong>May 2026</strong></p><p>‍</p></div></header></div></div></div></div></div></section></div>"},{"tag":"section","attrs":{"lottie":"trigger-scroll","className":"section_newsletter text-color-white"},"html":"<div class=\"padding-global\"><div class=\"padding-section-large\"><div class=\"wrapper_wide-screen\"><div class=\"container-large\"><div class=\"cta17_component\"><div class=\"w-layout-grid cta17_content\"><div class=\"newsletter_content-left\"><h2 data-scroll-speed=\"0.025\" data-scroll